{"parentUuid":"959cecfd-a288-4a84-83d2-cde81f91ef3c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bab18d11-a54d-4359-a1e4-66e491360a7c","agentId":"a18902932a394df42","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YMEmC5LW5B28pTQCwiFT1q","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# <Directory name>\n2\t\n3\t> Per-directory README template. Fill in; delete sections that don't apply.\n4\t> Update only affected sections on later changes — diff, don't rewrite.\n5\t\n6\t## Purpose\n7\t\n8\tOne or two sentences: what this directory is responsible for and why it exists.\n9\t\n10\t## Modules\n11\t\n12\t| File / module | Responsibility |\n13\t|---|---|\n14\t| `<file>` | <one line> |\n15\t\n16\t## Relationships\n17\t\n18\tHow the modules here relate to each other and to the rest of the system. Note\n19\tthe public surface (what other code imports) versus internals hidden behind it.\n20\tIf this directory is a facade (auth, logging, config), say so and name the\n21\tpublic entry points.\n22\t\n23\t## Notes (optional)\n24\t\n25\tNon-obvious constraints, env vars consumed, or gotchas a maintainer needs.\n26\t"}]},"uuid":"ce626925-c17c-4ea7-8ba9-e295695eab23","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:32:03.280Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/brett/.claude/skills/doc-conventions/readme-template.md","content":"# <Directory name>\n\n> Per-directory README template. Fill in; delete sections that don't apply.\n> Update only affected sections on later changes — diff, don't rewrite.\n\n## Purpose\n\nOne or two sentences: what this directory is responsible for and why it exists.\n\n## Modules\n\n| File / module | Responsibility |\n|---|---|\n| `<file>` | <one line> |\n\n## Relationships\n\nHow the modules here relate to each other and to the rest of the system. Note\nthe public surface (what other code imports) versus internals hidden behind it.\nIf this directory is a facade (auth, logging, config), say so and name the\npublic entry points.\n\n## Notes (optional)\n\nNon-obvious constraints, env vars consumed, or gotchas a maintainer needs.\n","numLines":26,"startLine":1,"totalLines":26}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"959cecfd-a288-4a84-83d2-cde81f91ef3c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
