{"parentUuid":"bd9bde53-33d4-43f3-b3ab-541714469412","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bab18d11-a54d-4359-a1e4-66e491360a7c","agentId":"a18902932a394df42","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E2NjzEiApEiY9dLxWAkQqm","type":"tool_result","content":"yes\nyes","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"210e0170-78d8-4d47-b083-662d8a445682","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:05.854Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"yes\nyes","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"bd9bde53-33d4-43f3-b3ab-541714469412","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"210e0170-78d8-4d47-b083-662d8a445682","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a18902932a394df42","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcwAcC4T33SJQ27BTysMm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01V8NA4YjruQV7477LL6Bse7","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/tests/README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":290,"cache_read_input_tokens":101356,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":290,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":56,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcwAcB1CazgiqZbmEGUKT","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"f7f6e556-76bb-4b7f-b791-943ea84828a9","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:07.745Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"f7f6e556-76bb-4b7f-b791-943ea84828a9","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bab18d11-a54d-4359-a1e4-66e491360a7c","agentId":"a18902932a394df42","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V8NA4YjruQV7477LL6Bse7","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# tests/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tUnit and fast component tests (no live Postgres/Redis) for the `src/` package,\n6\tplus the `tests/integration/` suite (real Postgres/Redis via testcontainers,\n7\tand real HTTP/k6 load). Mirrors `src/`'s layering: schema/crypto/time-window\n8\tunit tests here, endpoint/migration/concurrency/perf tests under `integration/`.\n9\t\n10\t## Modules\n11\t\n12\t| File | Responsibility |\n13\t|---|---|\n14\t| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures for the non-integration suite. |\n15\t| `test_app_smoke.py` | App-construction-level tests needing no DB/Redis: liveness, OpenAPI exposure, unauthenticated-denial/error-envelope shape. |\n16\t| `test_auth_api_key.py` | Split-token parsing and the in-process verification cache (Argon2id-vs-p95 cache mechanism). |\n17\t| `test_crypto.py` | `src/crypto` facade: Argon2id hash/verify, constant-time compare. |\n18\t| `test_csv_export.py` | `src/api/csv_export.py` unit tests: `escape_csv_text_cell` (formula-trigger prefixing incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, control-char stripping), RFC 4180 quoting via `csv.writer`, `format_window_start`/`format_total_quantity` value formatting (no scientific notation, UTC ISO-8601). |\n19\t| `test_dast_context_documented.py` | Asserts the DAST scanner auth context (header + token shape) is documented somewhere a DAST job's config can read it. |\n20\t| `test_db_session_isolation.py` | Regression guard for the `READ COMMITTED` isolation pin in `src/db/session.py` — the dependency the quota lock-then-read atomicity in `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::read_tenant_quota_state_locked` relies on. |\n21\t| `test_dependency_pins.py` | Security-regression guard against a starlette CVE-carrying downgrade (pinned version stays at the patched release). |\n22\t| `test_logging_redaction.py` | A raw `customer_id` (or other sensitive field) must never reach the rendered log line regardless of call site. |\n23\t| `test_rate_limit_fail_open.py` | Regression test for the Tier-2 rate-limit logging facade in `src/auth/rate_limit.py`. |\n24\t| `test_schemas_events.py` | Validation-contract tests for `EventCreateRequest`. |\n25\t| `test_schemas_quotas.py` | Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (anchored `customer_id`/`metric` allowlists, `limit_per_window` bounds, injection rejection) and `QuotaDeleteParams` (accept/missing/mass-assignment/injection-oversized/invalid-metric cases, plus a Hypothesis property test that acceptance implies the anchored regex). |\n26\t| `test_schemas_usage.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageQueryParams`. |\n27\t| `test_schemas_usage_export.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageExportQueryParams`: all-filters-optional, the `from`/`from_` alias binding, naive-datetime rejection, `from<=to` and `[now-90d, now+1h]` bound enforcement, `extra=\"forbid\"` rejecting unknown/injected fields. |\n28\t| `test_slo_alarms_defined.py` | Static assertion that the declared SLO burn-rate + canary CloudWatch alarms exist in the Terraform source with the exact names `deploy.yml` expects. |\n29\t| `test_time_windows.py` | Tests for the UTC hour-flooring helper (`floor_to_hour_utc`) shared by `events_service` and `usage_service`. |\n30\t| `test_usage_export_service.py` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` unit tests: `prepare_export` cap-boundary (exactly-at-cap passes, cap+1 → 422) and fail-closed non-cap-error propagation (AC22); `stream_export_csv` header-first-on-empty-result, audit-log fields (no raw `customer_id`), `completed=False` on a mid-stream failure, and the chunk-batching regression guard (`_ROWS_PER_CHUNK`). |\n31\t| `integration/` | Tests requiring a real Postgres/Redis (testcontainers) or a live HTTP process — see `tests/integration/README.md`. |\n32\t\n33\t## Relationships\n34\t\n35\t- Unit tests here import directly from `src.*` modules (schemas, crypto, auth, time\n36\t  windows) with no network/DB dependency — fast, run on every commit.\n37\t- `integration/` depends on Docker (testcontainers for Postgres/Redis, and for\n38\t  `test_perf_k6_load.py`, the `grafana/k6` image) and is slower; both suites are\n39\t  collected together by `pytest --cov=src --cov-branch` (per `CLAUDE.md`).\n40\t- Test IDs referenced in docstrings (`AC1`, `AC-PERF`, etc.) trace to\n41\t  `.pipeline/acceptance.md`'s acceptance criteria for the feature that introduced them.\n42\t"}]},"uuid":"2341747e-0898-447e-9f2a-4f7d8d3bfbf8","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:07.764Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/tests/README.md","content":"# tests/\n\n## Purpose\n\nUnit and fast component tests (no live Postgres/Redis) for the `src/` package,\nplus the `tests/integration/` suite (real Postgres/Redis via testcontainers,\nand real HTTP/k6 load). Mirrors `src/`'s layering: schema/crypto/time-window\nunit tests here, endpoint/migration/concurrency/perf tests under `integration/`.\n\n## Modules\n\n| File | Responsibility |\n|---|---|\n| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures for the non-integration suite. |\n| `test_app_smoke.py` | App-construction-level tests needing no DB/Redis: liveness, OpenAPI exposure, unauthenticated-denial/error-envelope shape. |\n| `test_auth_api_key.py` | Split-token parsing and the in-process verification cache (Argon2id-vs-p95 cache mechanism). |\n| `test_crypto.py` | `src/crypto` facade: Argon2id hash/verify, constant-time compare. |\n| `test_csv_export.py` | `src/api/csv_export.py` unit tests: `escape_csv_text_cell` (formula-trigger prefixing incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, control-char stripping), RFC 4180 quoting via `csv.writer`, `format_window_start`/`format_total_quantity` value formatting (no scientific notation, UTC ISO-8601). |\n| `test_dast_context_documented.py` | Asserts the DAST scanner auth context (header + token shape) is documented somewhere a DAST job's config can read it. |\n| `test_db_session_isolation.py` | Regression guard for the `READ COMMITTED` isolation pin in `src/db/session.py` — the dependency the quota lock-then-read atomicity in `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::read_tenant_quota_state_locked` relies on. |\n| `test_dependency_pins.py` | Security-regression guard against a starlette CVE-carrying downgrade (pinned version stays at the patched release). |\n| `test_logging_redaction.py` | A raw `customer_id` (or other sensitive field) must never reach the rendered log line regardless of call site. |\n| `test_rate_limit_fail_open.py` | Regression test for the Tier-2 rate-limit logging facade in `src/auth/rate_limit.py`. |\n| `test_schemas_events.py` | Validation-contract tests for `EventCreateRequest`. |\n| `test_schemas_quotas.py` | Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (anchored `customer_id`/`metric` allowlists, `limit_per_window` bounds, injection rejection) and `QuotaDeleteParams` (accept/missing/mass-assignment/injection-oversized/invalid-metric cases, plus a Hypothesis property test that acceptance implies the anchored regex). |\n| `test_schemas_usage.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageQueryParams`. |\n| `test_schemas_usage_export.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageExportQueryParams`: all-filters-optional, the `from`/`from_` alias binding, naive-datetime rejection, `from<=to` and `[now-90d, now+1h]` bound enforcement, `extra=\"forbid\"` rejecting unknown/injected fields. |\n| `test_slo_alarms_defined.py` | Static assertion that the declared SLO burn-rate + canary CloudWatch alarms exist in the Terraform source with the exact names `deploy.yml` expects. |\n| `test_time_windows.py` | Tests for the UTC hour-flooring helper (`floor_to_hour_utc`) shared by `events_service` and `usage_service`. |\n| `test_usage_export_service.py` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` unit tests: `prepare_export` cap-boundary (exactly-at-cap passes, cap+1 → 422) and fail-closed non-cap-error propagation (AC22); `stream_export_csv` header-first-on-empty-result, audit-log fields (no raw `customer_id`), `completed=False` on a mid-stream failure, and the chunk-batching regression guard (`_ROWS_PER_CHUNK`). |\n| `integration/` | Tests requiring a real Postgres/Redis (testcontainers) or a live HTTP process — see `tests/integration/README.md`. |\n\n## Relationships\n\n- Unit tests here import directly from `src.*` modules (schemas, crypto, auth, time\n  windows) with no network/DB dependency — fast, run on every commit.\n- `integration/` depends on Docker (testcontainers for Postgres/Redis, and for\n  `test_perf_k6_load.py`, the `grafana/k6` image) and is slower; both suites are\n  collected together by `pytest --cov=src --cov-branch` (per `CLAUDE.md`).\n- Test IDs referenced in docstrings (`AC1`, `AC-PERF`, etc.) trace to\n  `.pipeline/acceptance.md`'s acceptance criteria for the feature that introduced them.\n","numLines":42,"startLine":1,"totalLines":42}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f7f6e556-76bb-4b7f-b791-943ea84828a9","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"2341747e-0898-447e-9f2a-4f7d8d3bfbf8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a18902932a394df42","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcwAcC4T33SJQ27BTysMm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EyUJe9WbMDJ7A69rih6yNM","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/tests/integration/README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":290,"cache_read_input_tokens":101356,"output_tokens":184,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":290},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":184,"cache_read_input_tokens":101356,"cache_creation_input_tokens":290,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":290,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcwAcB1CazgiqZbmEGUKT","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"5514a794-af91-4cf3-a198-d0663497bd20","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:08.175Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"5514a794-af91-4cf3-a198-d0663497bd20","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bab18d11-a54d-4359-a1e4-66e491360a7c","agentId":"a18902932a394df42","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EyUJe9WbMDJ7A69rih6yNM","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# tests/integration/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tIntegration tests that exercise the app against real dependencies: Postgres and\n6\tRedis via testcontainers, a live out-of-process uvicorn for perf/load tests, and\n7\tAlembic migrations run against a scratch database. Complements the fast unit\n8\tsuite in `tests/` (no live DB/Redis there).\n9\t\n10\t## Modules\n11\t\n12\t| File | Responsibility |\n13\t|---|---|\n14\t| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures: testcontainer Postgres/Redis setup, the FastAPI test client, seeded `api_keys` rows. |\n15\t| `test_concurrency.py` | 50 concurrent same-`idempotency_key` POSTs create exactly one `events` row (idempotency under concurrency). |\n16\t| `test_data_protection.py` | `api_keys.secret_hash` is persisted as an Argon2id hash, never plaintext; the normal auth path still verifies end to end. |\n17\t| `test_events_endpoint.py` | `POST /v1/events` integration tests (create, replay, validation, auth). |\n18\t| `test_events_quota_enforcement.py` | `POST /v1/events` quota-check integration tests: unlimited-without-a-quota, under/at/over-limit, replay-bypasses-quota, mid-window quota change, throttle-vs-quota distinct error codes. |\n19\t| `test_health_readiness.py` | `/health/ready` against a live, migrated Postgres. |\n20\t| `test_migrations.py` | Migration round-trip (`0001`/`0002`) on a prod-shaped seeded dataset, own scratch testcontainer. |\n21\t| `test_perf_k6_load.py` | Sustained k6 load (via Docker) against a real out-of-process uvicorn; drives both the no-quota baseline and the quota-active scenario at equal worker budget for the AC20 relative p95 comparison. |\n22\t| `test_perf_smoke.py` | Smoke-sized perf check (no k6/Locust dependency) against a live uvicorn process. |\n23\t| `test_quota_concurrency.py` | N concurrent distinct-`idempotency_key` posts against a quota cap `L` never drive the rollup total above `L` (`FOR UPDATE` row-lock serialization proof). |\n24\t| `test_quota_migration.py` | Migration `0003` (`quotas` table + `api_keys.scope`) round-trip and constraint re-enforcement. |\n25\t| `test_quotas_endpoint.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` integration tests: create/replace, auth, admin-scope enforcement, validation, tenant isolation, rate limiting, OpenAPI exposure. |\n26\t| `test_quotas_list_delete.py` | `GET /v1/quotas` and `DELETE /v1/quotas` integration tests: GET ordering + minimal fields, tenant isolation, empty-list 200, ingest-key 403, no-auth 401; DELETE 204 + row removed, 404 on absent, cross-tenant 404 with the victim row intact, validation 422, ingest-key 403, no-auth 401, `quota.delete`/`quota.forbidden` logging; the two-principals-one-IP Tier-2 rate-limit shape on both verbs; the no-usage-reset / uncapped-events-accepted cross-behavior; the safe-error / fail-closed 500 path on both verbs (AC19); a concurrent-DELETE-of-the-same-row race (exactly one winner); and OpenAPI exposure of both new verbs. |\n27\t| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates/deletes to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. `test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent` (new, quota-admin feature) is the DELETE-specific backstop proof, mirroring the existing read/update cases. |\n28\t| `test_rate_limit.py` | Tier-2 (`api_key_id`-keyed) rate limiting: two principals on one IP get independent buckets; one principal across two IPs shares one bucket. |\n29\t| `test_seed_api_key_script.py` | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` provisions a key against a real database, including the `--admin` flag setting `scope='admin'` (default `scope='ingest'`). |\n30\t| `test_usage_endpoint.py` | `GET /v1/usage` integration tests (aggregation, tenant isolation). |\n31\t| `test_usage_export_endpoint.py` | `GET /v1/usage/export` integration tests: header-only-CSV on an empty result, per-filter narrowing, deterministic ordering, two-tenant isolation, row-cap 422 with no partial body, formula-injection escape end-to-end, response headers (content-type/filename/nosniff/no-store), streaming-not-buffered (multi-chunk) sanity, OpenAPI-schema exposure (AC19), the seeded DAST key calling the export via `test_export_seeded_dast_key_can_call_the_export` (AC20), and the fail-closed pre-flight 500 on a forced `COUNT` error (AC22). |\n32\t| `test_usage_export_perf.py` | Real-Postgres-testcontainer p95 timing sanity check for the export at the 100,000-row cap (AC16) — a 10-sample stable measurement asserting the human-confirmed `p95 <= 3,000ms` bound (not a k6 load test). |\n33\t| `k6/` | k6 load-test scripts driven by `test_perf_k6_load.py` — see `k6/README.md`. |\n34\t\n35\t## Relationships\n36\t\n37\t- All DB-backed tests share the Postgres/Redis testcontainer fixtures from `conftest.py`,\n38\t  except `test_migrations.py` and `test_quota_migration.py`, which own a scratch\n39\t  testcontainer independently (they drive the migration lifecycle itself: down to a\n40\t  prior revision and back up, which the shared fixture's already-migrated database\n41\t  can't support).\n42\t- `test_perf_k6_load.py` and `k6/load_events_quota.js` work as a pair: the Python test\n43\t  starts uvicorn, seeds fixture data (including quota rows for the quota-active run),\n44\t  invokes the k6 script via Docker, and asserts against the JSON summary it produces.\n45\t- Docstring AC references (`AC7`, `AC13`, `AC16`, `AC20`, etc.) trace to\n46\t  `.pipeline/acceptance.md`.\n47\t"}]},"uuid":"b038e6e4-c1d1-48d9-b310-da0b70757e63","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:08.187Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/tests/integration/README.md","content":"# tests/integration/\n\n## Purpose\n\nIntegration tests that exercise the app against real dependencies: Postgres and\nRedis via testcontainers, a live out-of-process uvicorn for perf/load tests, and\nAlembic migrations run against a scratch database. Complements the fast unit\nsuite in `tests/` (no live DB/Redis there).\n\n## Modules\n\n| File | Responsibility |\n|---|---|\n| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures: testcontainer Postgres/Redis setup, the FastAPI test client, seeded `api_keys` rows. |\n| `test_concurrency.py` | 50 concurrent same-`idempotency_key` POSTs create exactly one `events` row (idempotency under concurrency). |\n| `test_data_protection.py` | `api_keys.secret_hash` is persisted as an Argon2id hash, never plaintext; the normal auth path still verifies end to end. |\n| `test_events_endpoint.py` | `POST /v1/events` integration tests (create, replay, validation, auth). |\n| `test_events_quota_enforcement.py` | `POST /v1/events` quota-check integration tests: unlimited-without-a-quota, under/at/over-limit, replay-bypasses-quota, mid-window quota change, throttle-vs-quota distinct error codes. |\n| `test_health_readiness.py` | `/health/ready` against a live, migrated Postgres. |\n| `test_migrations.py` | Migration round-trip (`0001`/`0002`) on a prod-shaped seeded dataset, own scratch testcontainer. |\n| `test_perf_k6_load.py` | Sustained k6 load (via Docker) against a real out-of-process uvicorn; drives both the no-quota baseline and the quota-active scenario at equal worker budget for the AC20 relative p95 comparison. |\n| `test_perf_smoke.py` | Smoke-sized perf check (no k6/Locust dependency) against a live uvicorn process. |\n| `test_quota_concurrency.py` | N concurrent distinct-`idempotency_key` posts against a quota cap `L` never drive the rollup total above `L` (`FOR UPDATE` row-lock serialization proof). |\n| `test_quota_migration.py` | Migration `0003` (`quotas` table + `api_keys.scope`) round-trip and constraint re-enforcement. |\n| `test_quotas_endpoint.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` integration tests: create/replace, auth, admin-scope enforcement, validation, tenant isolation, rate limiting, OpenAPI exposure. |\n| `test_quotas_list_delete.py` | `GET /v1/quotas` and `DELETE /v1/quotas` integration tests: GET ordering + minimal fields, tenant isolation, empty-list 200, ingest-key 403, no-auth 401; DELETE 204 + row removed, 404 on absent, cross-tenant 404 with the victim row intact, validation 422, ingest-key 403, no-auth 401, `quota.delete`/`quota.forbidden` logging; the two-principals-one-IP Tier-2 rate-limit shape on both verbs; the no-usage-reset / uncapped-events-accepted cross-behavior; the safe-error / fail-closed 500 path on both verbs (AC19); a concurrent-DELETE-of-the-same-row race (exactly one winner); and OpenAPI exposure of both new verbs. |\n| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates/deletes to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. `test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent` (new, quota-admin feature) is the DELETE-specific backstop proof, mirroring the existing read/update cases. |\n| `test_rate_limit.py` | Tier-2 (`api_key_id`-keyed) rate limiting: two principals on one IP get independent buckets; one principal across two IPs shares one bucket. |\n| `test_seed_api_key_script.py` | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` provisions a key against a real database, including the `--admin` flag setting `scope='admin'` (default `scope='ingest'`). |\n| `test_usage_endpoint.py` | `GET /v1/usage` integration tests (aggregation, tenant isolation). |\n| `test_usage_export_endpoint.py` | `GET /v1/usage/export` integration tests: header-only-CSV on an empty result, per-filter narrowing, deterministic ordering, two-tenant isolation, row-cap 422 with no partial body, formula-injection escape end-to-end, response headers (content-type/filename/nosniff/no-store), streaming-not-buffered (multi-chunk) sanity, OpenAPI-schema exposure (AC19), the seeded DAST key calling the export via `test_export_seeded_dast_key_can_call_the_export` (AC20), and the fail-closed pre-flight 500 on a forced `COUNT` error (AC22). |\n| `test_usage_export_perf.py` | Real-Postgres-testcontainer p95 timing sanity check for the export at the 100,000-row cap (AC16) — a 10-sample stable measurement asserting the human-confirmed `p95 <= 3,000ms` bound (not a k6 load test). |\n| `k6/` | k6 load-test scripts driven by `test_perf_k6_load.py` — see `k6/README.md`. |\n\n## Relationships\n\n- All DB-backed tests share the Postgres/Redis testcontainer fixtures from `conftest.py`,\n  except `test_migrations.py` and `test_quota_migration.py`, which own a scratch\n  testcontainer independently (they drive the migration lifecycle itself: down to a\n  prior revision and back up, which the shared fixture's already-migrated database\n  can't support).\n- `test_perf_k6_load.py` and `k6/load_events_quota.js` work as a pair: the Python test\n  starts uvicorn, seeds fixture data (including quota rows for the quota-active run),\n  invokes the k6 script via Docker, and asserts against the JSON summary it produces.\n- Docstring AC references (`AC7`, `AC13`, `AC16`, `AC20`, etc.) trace to\n  `.pipeline/acceptance.md`.\n","numLines":47,"startLine":1,"totalLines":47}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5514a794-af91-4cf3-a198-d0663497bd20","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
