{"parentUuid":"0d34b0e9-72bc-42b7-813f-5bf207bc7412","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bbf2c5d4-ec30-40d4-8674-2f3ba817b4ee","agentId":"a18902932a394df42","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NT4C6yZdWd7qrcFNDDAvky","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/docs/system_architecture.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"uuid":"5512c531-fcce-455d-a710-bbb7a748ae75","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:37.537Z","toolUseResult":{"filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/docs/system_architecture.md","oldString":"    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage: read rollup\"| EventsDB\n    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage/export: pre-flight COUNT + streamed SELECT\"| EventsDB\n    FastAPI -->|\"PUT /v1/quotas: upsert cap\"| EventsDB","newString":"    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage: read rollup\"| EventsDB\n    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage/daily: aggregate rollup by day+metric\"| EventsDB\n    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage/export: pre-flight COUNT + streamed SELECT\"| EventsDB\n    FastAPI -->|\"PUT /v1/quotas: upsert cap\"| EventsDB","originalFile":null,"structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":25,"oldLines":6,"newStart":25,"newLines":7,"lines":["     FastAPI -->|\"require_api_key: cache hit or Argon2id verify\"| AuthDB[(RDS PostgreSQL: api_keys)]","     FastAPI -->|\"POST /v1/events: insert + quota check + rollup upsert\"| EventsDB[(RDS PostgreSQL: events / usage_rollup / quotas)]","     FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage: read rollup\"| EventsDB","+    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage/daily: aggregate rollup by day+metric\"| EventsDB","     FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage/export: pre-flight COUNT + streamed SELECT\"| EventsDB","     FastAPI -->|\"PUT /v1/quotas: upsert cap\"| EventsDB","     FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/quotas: list caller's caps\"| EventsDB"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0d34b0e9-72bc-42b7-813f-5bf207bc7412","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"5512c531-fcce-455d-a710-bbb7a748ae75","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a18902932a394df42","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcwAeXhht2onx7cEQ6Pqk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now add the new request-flow section for `GET /v1/usage/daily`, after the `GET /v1/usage` section and before `GET /v1/usage/export`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1334,"cache_read_input_tokens":108329,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1334,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcwAeWXG4VbLygCARLFVs","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"3960d5b5-b5d9-46a1-a6ab-43acc89e6e3c","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:39.347Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"3960d5b5-b5d9-46a1-a6ab-43acc89e6e3c","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a18902932a394df42","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcwAeXhht2onx7cEQ6Pqk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LY7b4T85KasX1NEkxBedq8","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/docs/system_architecture.md","old_string":"## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/export`","new_string":"## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/daily`\n\nSame auth/throttle/error stack as `GET /v1/usage`, kept in its own sibling\nmodule (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`) so `GET /v1/usage`'s code path stays\nbyte-for-byte unchanged (`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`,\n`src/services/usage_daily_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`):\n\n1. `DailyUsageQueryParams` binds the single `date` query field as a loose\n   `str | None` (`extra=\"forbid\"` still rejects any undeclared param, e.g. a\n   smuggled `customer_id`, with the house 422 contract). `parse_daily_date`\n   then validates the *value* imperatively and raises `HTTPException(400)`\n   directly for a missing value, a non-`YYYY-MM-DD` shape, an invalid\n   calendar date, or a date outside `[today_utc-90d, today_utc+1d]` — the\n   endpoint's one deliberate 400-not-422 deviation from `usage.py`'s/\n   `usage_export.py`'s Pydantic-422 convention.\n2. `usage_daily_service.get_daily_usage` opens a `scoped_transaction` (the\n   same `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id` RLS-context mechanism every other\n   read/write uses) and calls `usage_repo.aggregate_daily_event_counts`,\n   which sums `usage_rollup.event_count` per `metric` over the half-open\n   `[day_start, day_end)` UTC window, scoped by `api_key_id` first\n   (`GROUP BY metric ORDER BY metric ASC` — one grouped aggregate over the\n   day's pre-computed hour-buckets, not a `COUNT(*)` scan of raw `events`).\n3. Logs one `usage.daily.read` event (`userId`, `action=\"read\"`,\n   `resource=\"usage_rollup\"`, `date`, `metricCount` — never `customer_id`),\n   then returns `DailyUsageResponse{date, metrics: [DailyMetricCount{metric,\n   event_count}, ...]}`. A day with no events returns 200 with `metrics: []`,\n   never 404 (the same \"absence is a valid answer\" contract `GET /v1/usage`\n   documents). An unexpected repository failure propagates uncaught to the\n   central `handle_unexpected_error` boundary — a generic fail-closed 500.\n\n**Customer-scoped, not admin-gated** — like `GET /v1/usage`, any authenticated\nkey may read its own daily summary; the endpoint accepts no `customer_id`/\n`api_key_id` input, which removes the IDOR parameter entirely.\n\n## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/export`"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1334,"cache_read_input_tokens":108329,"output_tokens":1175,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1334},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1175,"cache_read_input_tokens":108329,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1334,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1334,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcwAeWXG4VbLygCARLFVs","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"e34a0366-8ab4-421d-9db0-bcc0863e96ef","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:48.460Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"e34a0366-8ab4-421d-9db0-bcc0863e96ef","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bbf2c5d4-ec30-40d4-8674-2f3ba817b4ee","agentId":"a18902932a394df42","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LY7b4T85KasX1NEkxBedq8","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/docs/system_architecture.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"uuid":"027e2b24-b020-4aa5-a512-94d849064b63","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:50:48.692Z","toolUseResult":{"filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/docs/system_architecture.md","oldString":"## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/export`","newString":"## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/daily`\n\nSame auth/throttle/error stack as `GET /v1/usage`, kept in its own sibling\nmodule (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`) so `GET /v1/usage`'s code path stays\nbyte-for-byte unchanged (`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`,\n`src/services/usage_daily_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`):\n\n1. `DailyUsageQueryParams` binds the single `date` query field as a loose\n   `str | None` (`extra=\"forbid\"` still rejects any undeclared param, e.g. a\n   smuggled `customer_id`, with the house 422 contract). `parse_daily_date`\n   then validates the *value* imperatively and raises `HTTPException(400)`\n   directly for a missing value, a non-`YYYY-MM-DD` shape, an invalid\n   calendar date, or a date outside `[today_utc-90d, today_utc+1d]` — the\n   endpoint's one deliberate 400-not-422 deviation from `usage.py`'s/\n   `usage_export.py`'s Pydantic-422 convention.\n2. `usage_daily_service.get_daily_usage` opens a `scoped_transaction` (the\n   same `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id` RLS-context mechanism every other\n   read/write uses) and calls `usage_repo.aggregate_daily_event_counts`,\n   which sums `usage_rollup.event_count` per `metric` over the half-open\n   `[day_start, day_end)` UTC window, scoped by `api_key_id` first\n   (`GROUP BY metric ORDER BY metric ASC` — one grouped aggregate over the\n   day's pre-computed hour-buckets, not a `COUNT(*)` scan of raw `events`).\n3. Logs one `usage.daily.read` event (`userId`, `action=\"read\"`,\n   `resource=\"usage_rollup\"`, `date`, `metricCount` — never `customer_id`),\n   then returns `DailyUsageResponse{date, metrics: [DailyMetricCount{metric,\n   event_count}, ...]}`. A day with no events returns 200 with `metrics: []`,\n   never 404 (the same \"absence is a valid answer\" contract `GET /v1/usage`\n   documents). An unexpected repository failure propagates uncaught to the\n   central `handle_unexpected_error` boundary — a generic fail-closed 500.\n\n**Customer-scoped, not admin-gated** — like `GET /v1/usage`, any authenticated\nkey may read its own daily summary; the endpoint accepts no `customer_id`/\n`api_key_id` input, which removes the IDOR parameter entirely.\n\n## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/export`","originalFile":null,"structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":71,"oldLines":6,"newStart":71,"newLines":40,"lines":[" (`src/services/usage_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`). A missing"," bucket returns zeros with 200, never 404."," ","+## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/daily`","+","+Same auth/throttle/error stack as `GET /v1/usage`, kept in its own sibling","+module (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`) so `GET /v1/usage`'s code path stays","+byte-for-byte unchanged (`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`,","+`src/services/usage_daily_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`):","+","+1. `DailyUsageQueryParams` binds the single `date` query field as a loose","+   `str | None` (`extra=\"forbid\"` still rejects any undeclared param, e.g. a","+   smuggled `customer_id`, with the house 422 contract). `parse_daily_date`","+   then validates the *value* imperatively and raises `HTTPException(400)`","+   directly for a missing value, a non-`YYYY-MM-DD` shape, an invalid","+   calendar date, or a date outside `[today_utc-90d, today_utc+1d]` — the","+   endpoint's one deliberate 400-not-422 deviation from `usage.py`'s/","+   `usage_export.py`'s Pydantic-422 convention.","+2. `usage_daily_service.get_daily_usage` opens a `scoped_transaction` (the","+   same `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id` RLS-context mechanism every other","+   read/write uses) and calls `usage_repo.aggregate_daily_event_counts`,","+   which sums `usage_rollup.event_count` per `metric` over the half-open","+   `[day_start, day_end)` UTC window, scoped by `api_key_id` first","+   (`GROUP BY metric ORDER BY metric ASC` — one grouped aggregate over the","+   day's pre-computed hour-buckets, not a `COUNT(*)` scan of raw `events`).","+3. Logs one `usage.daily.read` event (`userId`, `action=\"read\"`,","+   `resource=\"usage_rollup\"`, `date`, `metricCount` — never `customer_id`),","+   then returns `DailyUsageResponse{date, metrics: [DailyMetricCount{metric,","+   event_count}, ...]}`. A day with no events returns 200 with `metrics: []`,","+   never 404 (the same \"absence is a valid answer\" contract `GET /v1/usage`","+   documents). An unexpected repository failure propagates uncaught to the","+   central `handle_unexpected_error` boundary — a generic fail-closed 500.","+","+**Customer-scoped, not admin-gated** — like `GET /v1/usage`, any authenticated","+key may read its own daily summary; the endpoint accepts no `customer_id`/","+`api_key_id` input, which removes the IDOR parameter entirely.","+"," ## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/export`"," "," Same auth/throttle/error stack, plus a two-phase pre-flight-then-stream"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e34a0366-8ab4-421d-9db0-bcc0863e96ef","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
