{"parentUuid":"d6cf7d20-f81b-4adf-9799-d55168f5970a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a18902932a394df42","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcwAox8t8sVACesPscTLH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XFW7HM35HJz7EajQtzphkF","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/pr-description.md","content":"# Add `GET /v1/usage/daily` — per-metric daily usage summary\n\n> Written to `.pipeline/pr-description.md` per the deployment gate's requirement\n> that this file exist.\n\n## Summary\n\nAdds a read-only, customer-scoped endpoint `GET /v1/usage/daily?date=YYYY-MM-DD`\nthat returns the authenticated tenant's per-metric event counts for one UTC\nday, aggregated from the pre-computed `usage_rollup` counters (not a\n`COUNT(*)` scan of raw `events`) — the same \"read the rollup\" discipline\n`GET /v1/usage` already follows. Delivered as a new sibling module trio\n(`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,\n`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`) plus one additive repository function\n(`usage_repo.aggregate_daily_event_counts`) and one `include_router` line in\n`src/main.py`, so every existing endpoint's code path is untouched — see the\nthreat model and full design rationale in `.pipeline/plan.md`.\n\nDuring implementation, security review surfaced and the debugging agent fixed\na pre-existing critical unrelated to the new read path itself: see\n**Sanctioned migration deviation** below.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **Schema** (`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`): `DailyUsageQueryParams`\n  (`date: str | None`, `extra=\"forbid\"`), `parse_daily_date` (imperative\n  400-on-invalid validation — missing, malformed, non-calendar, or outside\n  `[today_utc-90d, today_utc+1d]`), `day_window_for` (pure half-open\n  `[day_start, day_end)` UTC window arithmetic), `DailyUsageResponse` /\n  `DailyMetricCount`.\n- **Service** (`src/services/usage_daily_service.py`): `get_daily_usage`\n  validates the date, reads inside a `scoped_transaction`, logs\n  `usage.daily.read` (no `customer_id` in the log), returns `metrics: []`\n  (never 404) for an empty day.\n- **Route** (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`): `GET /v1/usage/daily`, auth ->\n  Tier-2 throttle (own sibling `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`, same\n  pattern as `usage.py`/`usage_export.py`) — customer-scoped, **not**\n  admin-gated (any authenticated key may read its own summary).\n- **Repository** (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`, additive): new\n  `aggregate_daily_event_counts(session, *, api_key_id, day_start, day_end)`\n  — `SELECT metric, SUM(event_count) ... GROUP BY metric ORDER BY metric ASC`,\n  scoped by `api_key_id` first (same IDOR/BOLA invariant as every other query\n  in this file), plus the `DailyMetricCount` dataclass it returns.\n- **Mount** (`src/main.py`, additive): one import + one\n  `app.include_router(usage_daily_router)` line.\n- **Security remediation** (see disclosure below): `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`,\n  `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py`.\n- **Docs**: READMEs for `src/api/routes/`, `src/api/schemas/` (new),\n  `src/services/`, `src/repositories/`, `alembic/`, `tests/`,\n  `tests/integration/` (updated); `docs/system_architecture.md` gained a new\n  `GET /v1/usage/daily` request-flow section, a Mermaid diagram edge, and a\n  `usage_rollup` data-model note for migration `0004`.\n\n## Disclosures (please read before approving)\n\n### 1. Sanctioned migration deviation\n\nThe plan declared **\"no new migration.\"** During security review, the\ndebugging agent's remediation added migration `0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`\nto fix a **pre-existing critical**: migration `0002` created `usage_rollup`\nwith `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` but not `FORCE`. The app connects as the\ntable **owner** `meterly_app`, and a PostgreSQL table owner **bypasses**\nnon-`FORCE` RLS regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS` — so the `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation`\npolicy (a named defense-in-depth backstop) was inert for the app role. This\nwas a real gap the new `GET /v1/usage/daily` read path would have exposed\n(the app-level `api_key_id` filter was still the sole effective isolation\ncontrol), so the remediation was scoped into this feature rather than\ndeferred.\n\n`0004` is **behavior-preserving**: it applies `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE\nROW LEVEL SECURITY` (a pure grant-semantics toggle, no DDL on rows/columns).\nEvery runtime reader/writer of `usage_rollup` — `usage_daily`, `usage_export`,\n`GET /v1/usage`, the quota `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` read, and the\n`POST /v1/events` rollup increment — already runs inside `scoped_transaction`,\nwhich issues `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id`; under `FORCE` each still sees\nexactly the rows the application `api_key_id` predicate already returns. It\nmirrors migration `0003`, which already applied `FORCE` to `quotas` for the\nsame owner-bypass reason. `test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py` proves the fix\nis genuinely effective, not merely present: it connects as a non-superuser\n**table owner** (the only role class whose RLS visibility actually flips on\n`FORCE`), removes the app-level `api_key_id` predicate entirely, and asserts\nthe owner is still confined to its own tenant's rows — falsified against a\ntemporarily-reverted `0004` this session (both new tests went RED without the\nfix, GREEN with it restored).\n\n### 2. Modified existing test\n\n`tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_no_new_alembic_migration_added`\n(a quota-admin AC14 guard) was updated to permit exactly the one sanctioned\n`0004` file, while preserving its real intent: it now inspects `0004`'s\nactual DDL targets (`ALTER TABLE (\\w+)`) and asserts they are `{\"usage_rollup\"}`\nonly, and that `0004` creates no table — so the guard still fails if any\nfuture migration smuggles a `quotas` schema change into this feature's story.\n\n### 3. DAST (Layer 1): effectively skipped — not representative\n\nThis run's DAST capture **could not bring the app up** in this environment (a\nWSL<->Windows localhost boot limitation — `dast-server.log` shows the capture\nscript failing to exec the configured `.venv/Scripts/python.exe` path, which\ndoes not exist under WSL). No DAST-clean verdict is being reported for this\nfeature. `.pipeline/dast-review.json` present in this pipeline run reflects\n**stale data from a prior feature's capture** (`dast-capture.json` is dated\n2026-07-10, a day before this feature's security/test runs) — it is **not**\na scan of the `usage-daily` change set and must not be read as one. The\ngating DAST layers run in CI against staging, not in this local run.\n\n### 4. Pre-existing out-of-scope item\n\nThe `events` table (migration `0001`) carries the same non-`FORCE`-RLS gap\nthat was just fixed for `usage_rollup` — `meterly_app` owns `events` too, so\n`events_tenant_isolation` is equally inert for the app role there. This was\n**deliberately left out of this feature's scope** (it's not on the\n`usage-daily` read path) and is tracked for the finding ledger as a follow-up.\n\n## Decisions & tradeoffs\n\n- **400, not 422, for a malformed/missing `date`.** The brief pins HTTP 400,\n  whereas the codebase's other query schemas surface validation failures as\n  422. `date` is bound as a loose `str | None` and validated imperatively by\n  `parse_daily_date`, which raises `HTTPException(400)` directly; an\n  *undeclared* query param still rides the house 422 path via `extra=\"forbid\"`.\n- **Aggregate the rollup, not `events`.** Keeps the per-request cost bounded\n  as ingest volume grows, matching `GET /v1/usage`'s existing design.\n- **Own sibling module, not added to `usage.py`.** Makes the no-behavior-change\n  claim for `GET /v1/usage` auditable by inspection of the diff rather than by\n  reasoning about a shared file (mirrors `usage_export.py`'s precedent).\n\n## Testing\n\n- **255/255 passed, 0 failed** (259 collected; 4 skipped — 3 k6-load\n  self-skips, `rc=255` in this environment, and 1 pre-existing perf test\n  deselected via `-m 'not perf'`, unrelated to this diff). `tested_change_hash`\n  in `.pipeline/test-results.json`: `046a6ed10e5aa5b91bb0ac5a7377a56444d0411c7e13a174b1d2ed07f2b012cf`.\n- **Acceptance criteria: 15 test-covered + 0 delegated to security** (all 15\n  of `AC1`-`AC15` are directly test-verified per `test-results.json`'s\n  `criteria_covered.by_id`; none carry `delegated: \"security\"`).\n- **Coverage (combined, `--cov-branch`):** lines 91.94%, **branches 93.59%**\n  — above the 85% `--cov-fail-under` gate. This feature's three new modules\n  (`schemas/usage_daily.py`, `routes/usage_daily.py`,\n  `services/usage_daily_service.py`) are 100% line-covered; the touched\n  `usage_repo.py` sits at 89% overall (the new `aggregate_daily_event_counts`\n  function's every branch is exercised — the miss is pre-existing\n  `usage`/`usage_export` lines untouched by this diff).\n- **Pyramid shape:** `test_strategy: pyramid`. New tests this feature: 25\n  unit (`tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py` — `parse_daily_date`/\n  `day_window_for`/schema validation, incl. a 10-case parametrized\n  malformed-date sweep) + 17 integration (15 in\n  `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py` covering AC1-AC15\n  end-to-end, plus 2 in `test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py` for the RLS\n  backstop, AC7).\n- **Test quality (advisory) — not applicable to this feature's own modules.**\n  `.pipeline/test-quality.json` exists but is **stale relative to this diff**:\n  it's dated 2026-07-10 (a day before this feature's security/test runs) and\n  its `mutation.configured_scope` targets the **quota-admin** modules\n  (`quotas_repo.py`, `quota_service.py`, `routes/quotas.py`,\n  `schemas/quotas.py`), not this feature's core modules (`schemas/usage_daily.py`,\n  `services/usage_daily_service.py`, `routes/usage_daily.py`, or the new\n  `aggregate_daily_event_counts` in `usage_repo.py`). No mutation score or\n  adversarial-gap data has actually been collected for `usage-daily`'s own\n  code — flagging this rather than presenting the quota-admin figures as if\n  they applied here. (For context, that stale run itself reports\n  `quality_ok: false` — mutmut can't run natively on Windows — plus five\n  low/medium adversarial gaps scoped to the quota endpoints.)\n\n## Security\n\n- Scope: diff since `791a37c`, re-scanned after the RLS remediation.\n  **Status: clean** — 0 critical, 0 warning, `stride_new_threats: 0`,\n  `stride_mechanisms_verified: 8/8`. Semgrep 8 findings, all triaged false\n  positives (test-only DDL role/table-identifier interpolation, unparameterizable\n  by construction, never reachable from request input). OSV 0 unfiltered\n  findings (no new dependency). See `.pipeline/security-report.md` for the\n  full findings inventory and ASVS reconciliation (`V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11,\n  V13, V16` triggered, all L1+L2 universal verified).\n- Threat model: see the `## Threat Model` section of `.pipeline/plan.md` —\n  Spoofing/Tampering/Information-Disclosure/DoS/EoP rows, all High-severity\n  threats mitigated (auth-before-data, bound-parameter SQL + anchored `date`\n  allowlist, `api_key_id`-only scoping with no IDOR parameter, dual-layer RLS\n  + app-level scoping for cross-tenant reads, fail-closed generic-500 error\n  envelope, Tier-1/Tier-2 throttling).\n\n## Supply chain\n\n- **Lockfile integrity:** clean (exit 0) — no manifest/lockfile drift, no\n  unpinned specifiers (`lockfile-check`, `.pipeline/security-report.md`).\n- **SBOM:** `.pipeline/sbom.cdx.json` is present (CycloneDX 1.7, Trivy\n  0.71.2, 65 components) but, like the DAST artifact above, its\n  `metadata.timestamp` (2026-07-10T02:33Z) predates this feature's\n  security/test runs and Trivy was explicitly **not** re-run this pass\n  (`security-report.md`: \"carried forward / skipped — no dependency change\n  this pass\"). No dependency changed in this diff (OSV confirms 0 new\n  findings against the current `poetry.lock`), so the component set is\n  expected to be current, but the SBOM file itself was not freshly generated\n  for this diff — noting for the deployment gate's file-existence check.\n\n## Design-record retention\n\nCopied this run's plan, acceptance criteria, plan-audit, security report, and\nrun-summary into `docs/decisions/feature/usage-daily/` (no `design-spec.md`\nthis run — `CLAUDE.md` declares \"Design source: none (API only)\"). Evidence\nfor humans/audits; no gate reads it.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":246,"cache_read_input_tokens":121456,"output_tokens":5040,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":246},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5040,"cache_read_input_tokens":121456,"cache_creation_input_tokens":246,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":246,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcwAovyg83fPw26gL22PF","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"e5c5ba06-f4bc-4c7d-898e-0ad2d5ad7639","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:53:26.661Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"e5c5ba06-f4bc-4c7d-898e-0ad2d5ad7639","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e8e302f4-f54d-442f-a953-ff8c41ca646f","agentId":"a18902932a394df42","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XFW7HM35HJz7EajQtzphkF","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/pr-description.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"uuid":"da3ce1f8-f7c6-4dd7-95f1-c0e88183db7f","timestamp":"2026-07-11T23:53:27.058Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"update","filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/pr-description.md","content":"# Add `GET /v1/usage/daily` — per-metric daily usage summary\n\n> Written to `.pipeline/pr-description.md` per the deployment gate's requirement\n> that this file exist.\n\n## Summary\n\nAdds a read-only, customer-scoped endpoint `GET /v1/usage/daily?date=YYYY-MM-DD`\nthat returns the authenticated tenant's per-metric event counts for one UTC\nday, aggregated from the pre-computed `usage_rollup` counters (not a\n`COUNT(*)` scan of raw `events`) — the same \"read the rollup\" discipline\n`GET /v1/usage` already follows. Delivered as a new sibling module trio\n(`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,\n`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`) plus one additive repository function\n(`usage_repo.aggregate_daily_event_counts`) and one `include_router` line in\n`src/main.py`, so every existing endpoint's code path is untouched — see the\nthreat model and full design rationale in `.pipeline/plan.md`.\n\nDuring implementation, security review surfaced and the debugging agent fixed\na pre-existing critical unrelated to the new read path itself: see\n**Sanctioned migration deviation** below.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **Schema** (`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`): `DailyUsageQueryParams`\n  (`date: str | None`, `extra=\"forbid\"`), `parse_daily_date` (imperative\n  400-on-invalid validation — missing, malformed, non-calendar, or outside\n  `[today_utc-90d, today_utc+1d]`), `day_window_for` (pure half-open\n  `[day_start, day_end)` UTC window arithmetic), `DailyUsageResponse` /\n  `DailyMetricCount`.\n- **Service** (`src/services/usage_daily_service.py`): `get_daily_usage`\n  validates the date, reads inside a `scoped_transaction`, logs\n  `usage.daily.read` (no `customer_id` in the log), returns `metrics: []`\n  (never 404) for an empty day.\n- **Route** (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`): `GET /v1/usage/daily`, auth ->\n  Tier-2 throttle (own sibling `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`, same\n  pattern as `usage.py`/`usage_export.py`) — customer-scoped, **not**\n  admin-gated (any authenticated key may read its own summary).\n- **Repository** (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`, additive): new\n  `aggregate_daily_event_counts(session, *, api_key_id, day_start, day_end)`\n  — `SELECT metric, SUM(event_count) ... GROUP BY metric ORDER BY metric ASC`,\n  scoped by `api_key_id` first (same IDOR/BOLA invariant as every other query\n  in this file), plus the `DailyMetricCount` dataclass it returns.\n- **Mount** (`src/main.py`, additive): one import + one\n  `app.include_router(usage_daily_router)` line.\n- **Security remediation** (see disclosure below): `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`,\n  `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py`.\n- **Docs**: READMEs for `src/api/routes/`, `src/api/schemas/` (new),\n  `src/services/`, `src/repositories/`, `alembic/`, `tests/`,\n  `tests/integration/` (updated); `docs/system_architecture.md` gained a new\n  `GET /v1/usage/daily` request-flow section, a Mermaid diagram edge, and a\n  `usage_rollup` data-model note for migration `0004`.\n\n## Disclosures (please read before approving)\n\n### 1. Sanctioned migration deviation\n\nThe plan declared **\"no new migration.\"** During security review, the\ndebugging agent's remediation added migration `0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`\nto fix a **pre-existing critical**: migration `0002` created `usage_rollup`\nwith `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` but not `FORCE`. The app connects as the\ntable **owner** `meterly_app`, and a PostgreSQL table owner **bypasses**\nnon-`FORCE` RLS regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS` — so the `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation`\npolicy (a named defense-in-depth backstop) was inert for the app role. This\nwas a real gap the new `GET /v1/usage/daily` read path would have exposed\n(the app-level `api_key_id` filter was still the sole effective isolation\ncontrol), so the remediation was scoped into this feature rather than\ndeferred.\n\n`0004` is **behavior-preserving**: it applies `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE\nROW LEVEL SECURITY` (a pure grant-semantics toggle, no DDL on rows/columns).\nEvery runtime reader/writer of `usage_rollup` — `usage_daily`, `usage_export`,\n`GET /v1/usage`, the quota `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` read, and the\n`POST /v1/events` rollup increment — already runs inside `scoped_transaction`,\nwhich issues `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id`; under `FORCE` each still sees\nexactly the rows the application `api_key_id` predicate already returns. It\nmirrors migration `0003`, which already applied `FORCE` to `quotas` for the\nsame owner-bypass reason. `test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py` proves the fix\nis genuinely effective, not merely present: it connects as a non-superuser\n**table owner** (the only role class whose RLS visibility actually flips on\n`FORCE`), removes the app-level `api_key_id` predicate entirely, and asserts\nthe owner is still confined to its own tenant's rows — falsified against a\ntemporarily-reverted `0004` this session (both new tests went RED without the\nfix, GREEN with it restored).\n\n### 2. Modified existing test\n\n`tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_no_new_alembic_migration_added`\n(a quota-admin AC14 guard) was updated to permit exactly the one sanctioned\n`0004` file, while preserving its real intent: it now inspects `0004`'s\nactual DDL targets (`ALTER TABLE (\\w+)`) and asserts they are `{\"usage_rollup\"}`\nonly, and that `0004` creates no table — so the guard still fails if any\nfuture migration smuggles a `quotas` schema change into this feature's story.\n\n### 3. DAST (Layer 1): effectively skipped — not representative\n\nThis run's DAST capture **could not bring the app up** in this environment (a\nWSL<->Windows localhost boot limitation — `dast-server.log` shows the capture\nscript failing to exec the configured `.venv/Scripts/python.exe` path, which\ndoes not exist under WSL). No DAST-clean verdict is being reported for this\nfeature. `.pipeline/dast-review.json` present in this pipeline run reflects\n**stale data from a prior feature's capture** (`dast-capture.json` is dated\n2026-07-10, a day before this feature's security/test runs) — it is **not**\na scan of the `usage-daily` change set and must not be read as one. The\ngating DAST layers run in CI against staging, not in this local run.\n\n### 4. Pre-existing out-of-scope item\n\nThe `events` table (migration `0001`) carries the same non-`FORCE`-RLS gap\nthat was just fixed for `usage_rollup` — `meterly_app` owns `events` too, so\n`events_tenant_isolation` is equally inert for the app role there. This was\n**deliberately left out of this feature's scope** (it's not on the\n`usage-daily` read path) and is tracked for the finding ledger as a follow-up.\n\n## Decisions & tradeoffs\n\n- **400, not 422, for a malformed/missing `date`.** The brief pins HTTP 400,\n  whereas the codebase's other query schemas surface validation failures as\n  422. `date` is bound as a loose `str | None` and validated imperatively by\n  `parse_daily_date`, which raises `HTTPException(400)` directly; an\n  *undeclared* query param still rides the house 422 path via `extra=\"forbid\"`.\n- **Aggregate the rollup, not `events`.** Keeps the per-request cost bounded\n  as ingest volume grows, matching `GET /v1/usage`'s existing design.\n- **Own sibling module, not added to `usage.py`.** Makes the no-behavior-change\n  claim for `GET /v1/usage` auditable by inspection of the diff rather than by\n  reasoning about a shared file (mirrors `usage_export.py`'s precedent).\n\n## Testing\n\n- **255/255 passed, 0 failed** (259 collected; 4 skipped — 3 k6-load\n  self-skips, `rc=255` in this environment, and 1 pre-existing perf test\n  deselected via `-m 'not perf'`, unrelated to this diff). `tested_change_hash`\n  in `.pipeline/test-results.json`: `046a6ed10e5aa5b91bb0ac5a7377a56444d0411c7e13a174b1d2ed07f2b012cf`.\n- **Acceptance criteria: 15 test-covered + 0 delegated to security** (all 15\n  of `AC1`-`AC15` are directly test-verified per `test-results.json`'s\n  `criteria_covered.by_id`; none carry `delegated: \"security\"`).\n- **Coverage (combined, `--cov-branch`):** lines 91.94%, **branches 93.59%**\n  — above the 85% `--cov-fail-under` gate. This feature's three new modules\n  (`schemas/usage_daily.py`, `routes/usage_daily.py`,\n  `services/usage_daily_service.py`) are 100% line-covered; the touched\n  `usage_repo.py` sits at 89% overall (the new `aggregate_daily_event_counts`\n  function's every branch is exercised — the miss is pre-existing\n  `usage`/`usage_export` lines untouched by this diff).\n- **Pyramid shape:** `test_strategy: pyramid`. New tests this feature: 25\n  unit (`tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py` — `parse_daily_date`/\n  `day_window_for`/schema validation, incl. a 10-case parametrized\n  malformed-date sweep) + 17 integration (15 in\n  `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py` covering AC1-AC15\n  end-to-end, plus 2 in `test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py` for the RLS\n  backstop, AC7).\n- **Test quality (advisory) — not applicable to this feature's own modules.**\n  `.pipeline/test-quality.json` exists but is **stale relative to this diff**:\n  it's dated 2026-07-10 (a day before this feature's security/test runs) and\n  its `mutation.configured_scope` targets the **quota-admin** modules\n  (`quotas_repo.py`, `quota_service.py`, `routes/quotas.py`,\n  `schemas/quotas.py`), not this feature's core modules (`schemas/usage_daily.py`,\n  `services/usage_daily_service.py`, `routes/usage_daily.py`, or the new\n  `aggregate_daily_event_counts` in `usage_repo.py`). No mutation score or\n  adversarial-gap data has actually been collected for `usage-daily`'s own\n  code — flagging this rather than presenting the quota-admin figures as if\n  they applied here. (For context, that stale run itself reports\n  `quality_ok: false` — mutmut can't run natively on Windows — plus five\n  low/medium adversarial gaps scoped to the quota endpoints.)\n\n## Security\n\n- Scope: diff since `791a37c`, re-scanned after the RLS remediation.\n  **Status: clean** — 0 critical, 0 warning, `stride_new_threats: 0`,\n  `stride_mechanisms_verified: 8/8`. Semgrep 8 findings, all triaged false\n  positives (test-only DDL role/table-identifier interpolation, unparameterizable\n  by construction, never reachable from request input). OSV 0 unfiltered\n  findings (no new dependency). See `.pipeline/security-report.md` for the\n  full findings inventory and ASVS reconciliation (`V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11,\n  V13, V16` triggered, all L1+L2 universal verified).\n- Threat model: see the `## Threat Model` section of `.pipeline/plan.md` —\n  Spoofing/Tampering/Information-Disclosure/DoS/EoP rows, all High-severity\n  threats mitigated (auth-before-data, bound-parameter SQL + anchored `date`\n  allowlist, `api_key_id`-only scoping with no IDOR parameter, dual-layer RLS\n  + app-level scoping for cross-tenant reads, fail-closed generic-500 error\n  envelope, Tier-1/Tier-2 throttling).\n\n## Supply chain\n\n- **Lockfile integrity:** clean (exit 0) — no manifest/lockfile drift, no\n  unpinned specifiers (`lockfile-check`, `.pipeline/security-report.md`).\n- **SBOM:** `.pipeline/sbom.cdx.json` is present (CycloneDX 1.7, Trivy\n  0.71.2, 65 components) but, like the DAST artifact above, its\n  `metadata.timestamp` (2026-07-10T02:33Z) predates this feature's\n  security/test runs and Trivy was explicitly **not** re-run this pass\n  (`security-report.md`: \"carried forward / skipped — no dependency change\n  this pass\"). No dependency changed in this diff (OSV confirms 0 new\n  findings against the current `poetry.lock`), so the component set is\n  expected to be current, but the SBOM file itself was not freshly generated\n  for this diff — noting for the deployment gate's file-existence check.\n\n## Design-record retention\n\nCopied this run's plan, acceptance criteria, plan-audit, security report, and\nrun-summary into `docs/decisions/feature/usage-daily/` (no `design-spec.md`\nthis run — `CLAUDE.md` declares \"Design source: none (API only)\"). Evidence\nfor humans/audits; no gate reads it.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":157,"newStart":1,"newLines":201,"lines":["-# Quota administration — GET /v1/quotas (list) + DELETE /v1/quotas (remove)","+# Add `GET /v1/usage/daily` — per-metric daily usage summary"," ","+> Written to `.pipeline/pr-description.md` per the deployment gate's requirement","+> that this file exist.","+"," ## Summary"," ","-Completes the quota-admin CRUD started by the shipped `metric-quotas` feature (`PUT /v1/quotas`).","-Adds two admin-scoped, tenant-isolated surfaces on the same `/v1/quotas` path: `GET /v1/quotas`","-returns the caller's full, unpaginated, deterministically ordered quota list; `DELETE","-/v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y` removes one cap, returning 204 on success or an explicit 404 if","-no such quota exists in the caller's tenant (not silently idempotent). Both reuse the existing","-`_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency chain, the same anchored `customer_id`/`metric`","-allowlists, `scoped_transaction`, and the `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE-RLS policy the shipped","-`PUT` already established — no new table, no new Alembic migration, no new credential, and no","-change to `POST /v1/events` behavior beyond deletion removing the cap (never the recorded","-`usage_rollup` counters). See `.pipeline/plan.md` for the full design rationale and its STRIDE","-threat model (also mirrored in `docs/system_architecture.md`'s \"Request flow — `GET`/`DELETE","-/v1/quotas`\" section).","+Adds a read-only, customer-scoped endpoint `GET /v1/usage/daily?date=YYYY-MM-DD`","+that returns the authenticated tenant's per-metric event counts for one UTC","+day, aggregated from the pre-computed `usage_rollup` counters (not a","+`COUNT(*)` scan of raw `events`) — the same \"read the rollup\" discipline","+`GET /v1/usage` already follows. Delivered as a new sibling module trio","+(`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,","+`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`) plus one additive repository function","+(`usage_repo.aggregate_daily_event_counts`) and one `include_router` line in","+`src/main.py`, so every existing endpoint's code path is untouched — see the","+threat model and full design rationale in `.pipeline/plan.md`."," ","+During implementation, security review surfaced and the debugging agent fixed","+a pre-existing critical unrelated to the new read path itself: see","+**Sanctioned migration deviation** below.","+"," ## Changes"," ","-- **API layer** (`src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/api/middleware.py`):","-  new `GET`/`DELETE /v1/quotas` handlers on the existing router; new `QuotaDeleteParams` query-param","-  schema (reuses `QuotaPutRequest`'s `CustomerId`/`Metric` allowlists, `extra='forbid'`); `DELETE`","-  added to CORS `allow_methods` (inert — empty origin allowlist, server-to-server API).","-- **Service layer** (`src/services/quota_service.py`): new `list_tenant_quotas(principal)` and","-  `delete_tenant_quota(principal, params)`; the latter raises `HTTPException(404)` on no match and","-  logs `quota.delete` INFO on success.","-- **Repository layer** (`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`): new `list_quotas(session, *,","-  api_key_id)` (ordered, tenant-scoped `SELECT`) and `delete_quota(session, *, api_key_id,","-  customer_id, metric)` (parameterized `DELETE ... RETURNING customer_id`, returns whether a row","-  matched).","-- **Security fix included in this diff** (found and fixed by the security stage, not part of the","-  planned feature scope): `.gitignore` was missing a `.terraform/` entry, so ~108 MB of vendored","-  Terraform provider binaries were entering the diff-scoped change set as untracked files. Added","-  `.terraform/` to `.gitignore`; the committable `infra/.terraform.lock.hcl` (provider pinning) is","-  deliberately left un-ignored.","-- **Docs**: this stage — `docs/system_architecture.md`, `src/api/README.md`,","-  `src/services/README.md`, `src/repositories/README.md`, `tests/README.md`,","-  `tests/integration/README.md`.","+- **Schema** (`src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`): `DailyUsageQueryParams`","+  (`date: str | None`, `extra=\"forbid\"`), `parse_daily_date` (imperative","+  400-on-invalid validation — missing, malformed, non-calendar, or outside","+  `[today_utc-90d, today_utc+1d]`), `day_window_for` (pure half-open","+  `[day_start, day_end)` UTC window arithmetic), `DailyUsageResponse` /","+  `DailyMetricCount`.","+- **Service** (`src/services/usage_daily_service.py`): `get_daily_usage`","+  validates the date, reads inside a `scoped_transaction`, logs","+  `usage.daily.read` (no `customer_id` in the log), returns `metrics: []`","+  (never 404) for an empty day.","+- **Route** (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`): `GET /v1/usage/daily`, auth ->","+  Tier-2 throttle (own sibling `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`, same","+  pattern as `usage.py`/`usage_export.py`) — customer-scoped, **not**","+  admin-gated (any authenticated key may read its own summary).","+- **Repository** (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`, additive): new","+  `aggregate_daily_event_counts(session, *, api_key_id, day_start, day_end)`","+  — `SELECT metric, SUM(event_count) ... GROUP BY metric ORDER BY metric ASC`,","+  scoped by `api_key_id` first (same IDOR/BOLA invariant as every other query","+  in this file), plus the `DailyMetricCount` dataclass it returns.","+- **Mount** (`src/main.py`, additive): one import + one","+  `app.include_router(usage_daily_router)` line.","+- **Security remediation** (see disclosure below): `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`,","+  `tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py`.","+- **Docs**: READMEs for `src/api/routes/`, `src/api/schemas/` (new),","+  `src/services/`, `src/repositories/`, `alembic/`, `tests/`,","+  `tests/integration/` (updated); `docs/system_architecture.md` gained a new","+  `GET /v1/usage/daily` request-flow section, a Mermaid diagram edge, and a","+  `usage_rollup` data-model note for migration `0004`."," ","-## Decisions & tradeoffs","+## Disclosures (please read before approving)"," ","-- **DELETE-not-found → 404, not idempotent-204.** A retried DELETE of an already-removed quota","-  returns 404 on the second call — the brief-sanctioned \"deletes are explicit\" contract, and","-  indistinguishable from a cross-tenant delete attempt (both correctly refuse to act; see BOLA note","-  below).","-- **No synchronization added between DELETE and an in-flight `POST /v1/events`.** Both contend on","-  the same quota-row lock (the DELETE's implicit lock vs. the ingest's `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE OF","-  q`), so PostgreSQL serializes them; whichever commits first determines the outcome for reads that","-  follow. This is the brief-accepted same race `PUT`'s replacement semantics already have — no","-  advisory lock, barrier, or usage reset was added.","-- **GET carries no dedicated audit log.** Plan's Open Question 1, resolved to \"no log\" — a plain","-  read of the caller's own config, mirroring `GET /v1/usage`'s precedent (reads don't emit business","-  events; DELETE, a destructive action, does).","-- **Unpaginated GET list.** Accepted per the brief on the assumption that per-tenant quota counts","-  stay small (bounded by admin `PUT` volume); pagination/filtering is a hard out-of-scope exclusion.","+### 1. Sanctioned migration deviation"," ","-## Testing","+The plan declared **\"no new migration.\"** During security review, the","+debugging agent's remediation added migration `0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`","+to fix a **pre-existing critical**: migration `0002` created `usage_rollup`","+with `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` but not `FORCE`. The app connects as the","+table **owner** `meterly_app`, and a PostgreSQL table owner **bypasses**","+non-`FORCE` RLS regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS` — so the `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation`","+policy (a named defense-in-depth backstop) was inert for the app role. This","+was a real gap the new `GET /v1/usage/daily` read path would have exposed","+(the app-level `api_key_id` filter was still the sole effective isolation","+control), so the remediation was scoped into this feature rather than","+deferred."," ","-**Acceptance criteria: 18 test-covered + 1 delegated to security = 19 total** (source:","-`.pipeline/test-results.json` `criteria_covered.by_id`; delegated = entries with `delegated:","-\"security\"`). AC18 (ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation across the change set) is the security stage's","-deliverable, not a test-suite assertion — confirmed reconciled in `.pipeline/security-report.md`","-(section 6g), not counted as test-covered.","+`0004` is **behavior-preserving**: it applies `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE","+ROW LEVEL SECURITY` (a pure grant-semantics toggle, no DDL on rows/columns).","+Every runtime reader/writer of `usage_rollup` — `usage_daily`, `usage_export`,","+`GET /v1/usage`, the quota `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` read, and the","+`POST /v1/events` rollup increment — already runs inside `scoped_transaction`,","+which issues `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id`; under `FORCE` each still sees","+exactly the rows the application `api_key_id` predicate already returns. It","+mirrors migration `0003`, which already applied `FORCE` to `quotas` for the","+same owner-bypass reason. `test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py` proves the fix","+is genuinely effective, not merely present: it connects as a non-superuser","+**table owner** (the only role class whose RLS visibility actually flips on","+`FORCE`), removes the app-level `api_key_id` predicate entirely, and asserts","+the owner is still confined to its own tenant's rows — falsified against a","+temporarily-reverted `0004` this session (both new tests went RED without the","+fix, GREEN with it restored)."," ","-- **Suite result:** 216/217 passed. The 1 failure —","-  `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py::test_export_p95_timing_meets_the_confirmed_3000ms_budget_at_the_row_cap`","-  — is a **pre-existing** hard-coded p95 timing assert from the already-merged `usage-export`","-  feature (last touched at `bcf16bb`, not in this branch's diff). It has no `@pytest.mark.perf`","-  marker, so it rides `pipeline-ci.yml`'s unfiltered test job. Re-measured this run at p95 3763ms vs.","-  its 3000ms budget, on a dev machine under concurrent Docker/CPU contention (four unrelated","-  containers running); this is a follow-up for the deployment/human owner, **not part of this","-  diff**.","-- **Coverage:** 88.15% lines, **66.67% branches** (combined; gate is `--cov-fail-under=85` on the","-  line figure, met). New/changed feature modules (`routes/quotas.py`, `schemas/quotas.py`,","-  `quota_service.py`) are 100% line-covered; `quotas_repo.py` sits at 71% branch coverage, attributed","-  in `test-results.json` to a coverage.py partial-branch artifact on multi-line return statements","-  that every call-path test does exercise (empty list, multi-row list, delete-found/not-found) —","-  matching an identical pre-existing pattern on the sibling `read_tenant_quota_state_locked`.","-- **Test-pyramid shape:** `pyramid` (project default), realized as 6 unit (schema validation) + 20","-  integration (endpoint/tenancy/concurrency/RLS-backstop) = 26 new tests this feature, out of 217","-  total in the full suite.","-- **Test quality (advisory — `.pipeline/test-quality.json`):** `quality_ok: false`. Mutation testing","-  (mutmut) **could not run** — it refuses to execute natively on Windows (the tool prints a","-  WSL-required message and exits without mutating anything; `scope: []`, not a silently-shrunk","-  measurement). The CI mutation job exists but is `if: false`-gated pending config; mutation coverage","-  for `quotas_repo.py`/`quota_service.py`/`routes/quotas.py`/`schemas/quotas.py` has genuinely never","-  run anywhere yet — flagged honestly rather than a false \"quality_ok: true\". Adversarial-review","-  notable gaps (all low severity except mutation, which is medium): DELETE's own 429 throttle","-  exhaustion is untested (only GET is driven to 429; DELETE is only proven *not* throttled while","-  under capacity); no wrong-type/repeated-query-param coercion test for DELETE's `customer_id`/","-  `metric`; ordering test doesn't probe a same-collation-adjacent-value case; the GET/DELETE","-  forced-error tests monkeypatch at the service layer, not inside the repository's own `text()`","-  execute call.","+### 2. Modified existing test"," ","-## Security","+`tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_no_new_alembic_migration_added`","+(a quota-admin AC14 guard) was updated to permit exactly the one sanctioned","+`0004` file, while preserving its real intent: it now inspects `0004`'s","+actual DDL targets (`ALTER TABLE (\\w+)`) and asserts they are `{\"usage_rollup\"}`","+only, and that `0004` creates no table — so the guard still fails if any","+future migration smuggles a `quotas` schema change into this feature's story."," ","-Scope: diff against `HEAD` (`ef3fb3f`). **Clean — 0 critical findings**, 2 non-blocking warnings:","-1. `CVE-2025-71176` (pytest 8.3.4, dev/test-only dependency, not in the runtime container) — CVSS","-   ~6.8, below the ≥7.0 deploy-gate floor. Safe version `>= 9.0.3`; not auto-bumped per policy (human","-   decides on `pyproject.toml`/`poetry.lock`).","-2. Pre-existing, out-of-diff-scope note: the Tier-1 pre-auth throttle keys on `request.client.host`","-   with no proxy-header trust configured, so behind the ALB it would bucket per-node rather than","-   per-real-client. Not introduced by this diff (only CORS `DELETE` touches `middleware.py` here);","-   the effective anti-abuse control for these admin routes is Tier-2 (principal-keyed, proven by","-   AC12).","+### 3. DAST (Layer 1): effectively skipped — not representative"," ","-STRIDE: 10/10 mechanisms verified present and efficacy-correct, 0 missing, 0 new unmodeled threats","-(`stride_new_threats: 0`). ASVS 5.0.0 reconciled across triggered chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V12/V13/","-V14/V16, including in-scope L3 V8.2.x (object-level authorization / BOLA), proven by the","-cross-tenant-DELETE→404 test (AC8) plus the adversarial RLS-backstop test that strips the","-`api_key_id` filter entirely and shows FORCE RLS alone still confines the DELETE","-(`test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent`).","+This run's DAST capture **could not bring the app up** in this environment (a","+WSL<->Windows localhost boot limitation — `dast-server.log` shows the capture","+script failing to exec the configured `.venv/Scripts/python.exe` path, which","+does not exist under WSL). No DAST-clean verdict is being reported for this","+feature. `.pipeline/dast-review.json` present in this pipeline run reflects","+**stale data from a prior feature's capture** (`dast-capture.json` is dated","+2026-07-10, a day before this feature's security/test runs) — it is **not**","+a scan of the `usage-daily` change set and must not be read as one. The","+gating DAST layers run in CI against staging, not in this local run."," ","-## Supply chain","+### 4. Pre-existing out-of-scope item"," ","-- **Lockfile integrity:** clean — no manifest/lockfile drift in the change set (`lockfile-check`).","-- **SBOM:** a CycloneDX SBOM was generated this run (`.pipeline/sbom.cdx.json`), **65 components**.","-  The deployment gate checks this file exists before allowing a deploy.","+The `events` table (migration `0001`) carries the same non-`FORCE`-RLS gap","+that was just fixed for `usage_rollup` — `meterly_app` owns `events` too, so","+`events_tenant_isolation` is equally inert for the app role there. This was","+**deliberately left out of this feature's scope** (it's not on the","+`usage-daily` read path) and is tracked for the finding ledger as a follow-up."," ","-## Design review (FE Layer 4)","+## Decisions & tradeoffs"," ","-Skipped — API-only project (`CLAUDE.md`: \"Design source: none\"), no design source (`design-approved`","-/ `design-spec.md`) and no `ui.env`. This is a deliberate non-trigger, not a silent gap: there is no","-UI surface for a visual-fidelity/a11y check to run against.","+- **400, not 422, for a malformed/missing `date`.** The brief pins HTTP 400,","+  whereas the codebase's other query schemas surface validation failures as","+  422. `date` is bound as a loose `str | None` and validated imperatively by","+  `parse_daily_date`, which raises `HTTPException(400)` directly; an","+  *undeclared* query param still rides the house 422 path via `extra=\"forbid\"`.","+- **Aggregate the rollup, not `events`.** Keeps the per-request cost bounded","+  as ingest volume grows, matching `GET /v1/usage`'s existing design.","+- **Own sibling module, not added to `usage.py`.** Makes the no-behavior-change","+  claim for `GET /v1/usage` auditable by inspection of the diff rather than by","+  reasoning about a shared file (mirrors `usage_export.py`'s precedent)."," ","-## DAST (runtime)","+## Testing"," ","-Advisory (`.pipeline/dast-review.json`) — OWASP ZAP passive baseline, `target_reached: true`","-(`http://host.docker.internal:8000`, status 200). Alert tally: 0 high, 3 medium, 4 low, 5","-informational. `over_budget: []`, `within_budget: true` — no severity band exceeded. This is a","-post-GREEN passive scan outside the security loop, not a pass/fail gate; the pre-merge scanners (see","-Security above) and human diff review remain the real teeth. Note: the **gating** DAST layers run in","-CI against staging, not in this local run.","+- **255/255 passed, 0 failed** (259 collected; 4 skipped — 3 k6-load","+  self-skips, `rc=255` in this environment, and 1 pre-existing perf test","+  deselected via `-m 'not perf'`, unrelated to this diff). `tested_change_hash`","+  in `.pipeline/test-results.json`: `046a6ed10e5aa5b91bb0ac5a7377a56444d0411c7e13a174b1d2ed07f2b012cf`.","+- **Acceptance criteria: 15 test-covered + 0 delegated to security** (all 15","+  of `AC1`-`AC15` are directly test-verified per `test-results.json`'s","+  `criteria_covered.by_id`; none carry `delegated: \"security\"`).","+- **Coverage (combined, `--cov-branch`):** lines 91.94%, **branches 93.59%**","+  — above the 85% `--cov-fail-under` gate. This feature's three new modules","+  (`schemas/usage_daily.py`, `routes/usage_daily.py`,","+  `services/usage_daily_service.py`) are 100% line-covered; the touched","+  `usage_repo.py` sits at 89% overall (the new `aggregate_daily_event_counts`","+  function's every branch is exercised — the miss is pre-existing","+  `usage`/`usage_export` lines untouched by this diff).","+- **Pyramid shape:** `test_strategy: pyramid`. New tests this feature: 25","+  unit (`tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py` — `parse_daily_date`/","+  `day_window_for`/schema validation, incl. a 10-case parametrized","+  malformed-date sweep) + 17 integration (15 in","+  `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py` covering AC1-AC15","+  end-to-end, plus 2 in `test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py` for the RLS","+  backstop, AC7).","+- **Test quality (advisory) — not applicable to this feature's own modules.**","+  `.pipeline/test-quality.json` exists but is **stale relative to this diff**:","+  it's dated 2026-07-10 (a day before this feature's security/test runs) and","+  its `mutation.configured_scope` targets the **quota-admin** modules","+  (`quotas_repo.py`, `quota_service.py`, `routes/quotas.py`,","+  `schemas/quotas.py`), not this feature's core modules (`schemas/usage_daily.py`,","+  `services/usage_daily_service.py`, `routes/usage_daily.py`, or the new","+  `aggregate_daily_event_counts` in `usage_repo.py`). No mutation score or","+  adversarial-gap data has actually been collected for `usage-daily`'s own","+  code — flagging this rather than presenting the quota-admin figures as if","+  they applied here. (For context, that stale run itself reports","+  `quality_ok: false` — mutmut can't run natively on Windows — plus five","+  low/medium adversarial gaps scoped to the quota endpoints.)"," ","-## Threat model","+## Security"," ","-See `.pipeline/plan.md` `## Threat Model` (STRIDE, scoped to this feature) for the full table and","-Mermaid DFD. Highest-severity items and their mitigations:","-- **Spoofing / EoP (function-level), High:** unauthenticated or non-admin caller hits GET/DELETE →","-  reused `_require_admin_and_throttled` (Argon2id auth + `scope=='admin'` gate → 403).","-- **Tampering (SQLi), High:** injection via `customer_id`/`metric` DELETE query params → anchored","-  `constr` allowlist rejects at the 422 boundary; parameterized `text()` bind params only.","-- **Info disclosure (GET response), High:** leaking internal fields or another tenant's caps →","-  minimal `response_model=list[QuotaResponse]` + `api_key_id`-scoped SELECT + FORCE RLS.","-- **EoP (IDOR/BOLA), High:** a key deletes another tenant's cap → `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS","-  means a cross-tenant DELETE matches zero rows → 404 (cannot see or remove the row at all); proven","-  by AC8 and the RLS-backstop adversarial test.","-- **Info disclosure (safe-error), Medium:** a forced DB exception on GET/DELETE → the existing","-  `handle_unexpected_error` generic-500 catch-all (no leak) + `scoped_transaction` rollback","-  (fail-closed, no partial DELETE) — new criterion AC19, added during the plan-audit revision pass","-  (see `.pipeline/plan-audit.md`).","+- Scope: diff since `791a37c`, re-scanned after the RLS remediation.","+  **Status: clean** — 0 critical, 0 warning, `stride_new_threats: 0`,","+  `stride_mechanisms_verified: 8/8`. Semgrep 8 findings, all triaged false","+  positives (test-only DDL role/table-identifier interpolation, unparameterizable","+  by construction, never reachable from request input). OSV 0 unfiltered","+  findings (no new dependency). See `.pipeline/security-report.md` for the","+  full findings inventory and ASVS reconciliation (`V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11,","+  V13, V16` triggered, all L1+L2 universal verified).","+- Threat model: see the `## Threat Model` section of `.pipeline/plan.md` —","+  Spoofing/Tampering/Information-Disclosure/DoS/EoP rows, all High-severity","+  threats mitigated (auth-before-data, bound-parameter SQL + anchored `date`","+  allowlist, `api_key_id`-only scoping with no IDOR parameter, dual-layer RLS","+  + app-level scoping for cross-tenant reads, fail-closed generic-500 error","+  envelope, Tier-1/Tier-2 throttling)."," ","+## Supply chain","+","+- **Lockfile integrity:** clean (exit 0) — no manifest/lockfile drift, no","+  unpinned specifiers (`lockfile-check`, `.pipeline/security-report.md`).","+- **SBOM:** `.pipeline/sbom.cdx.json` is present (CycloneDX 1.7, Trivy","+  0.71.2, 65 components) but, like the DAST artifact above, its","+  `metadata.timestamp` (2026-07-10T02:33Z) predates this feature's","+  security/test runs and Trivy was explicitly **not** re-run this pass","+  (`security-report.md`: \"carried forward / skipped — no dependency change","+  this pass\"). No dependency changed in this diff (OSV confirms 0 new","+  findings against the current `poetry.lock`), so the component set is","+  expected to be current, but the SBOM file itself was not freshly generated","+  for this diff — 